      <organization>Cisco</organization>
    </author>
    <date year="2020" month="March" day="9"/>
    <abstract>
      <t>While TLS 1.3 supports authentication with Pre-Shared Key (PSK), EAP- TLS with TLS 1.3 explicitly forbids PSK authentication except when used for resumption. This document specifies a separate EAP method (EAP-TLS-PSK) for use cases that require authentication based on external PSKs.</t>
    </abstract>
  </front>
